Vice President Mike Pence addressed the Faith and Freedom Coalition in Washington, D.C., praising their work and highlighting the achievements of the Trump administration. He mentioned the strong economy, low unemployment rates, and rising wages. Pence also discussed the administration's efforts to secure the border and address the crisis of illegal immigration. He criticized Democratic candidates for advocating open borders and offering free healthcare to illegal immigrants. Pence emphasized the importance of freedom and the dangers of socialism. He encouraged the audience to have faith in the American people and to continue fighting for conservative values. Pence concluded by asking for prayers for America and expressing gratitude for the opportunity to serve as Vice President.